Yes, a system of coupled pendulums is a good example from physics.
The following is a cool video showing how a system of coupled
metronomes (think of them as inverted pendulums) that start out with
different periods and phases synchronize eventually.

   http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tlYIyKic3w8

It demonstrates a couple of properties of coupled oscillators that are
useful for generating gaits: (1) synchronized oscillations, and (2)
robustness of such synchronization to small perturbations.

Vinod

